cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about text generation using a variational auto-encoder (VAE) with a Gaussian mixture distribution as the prior. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also proposes an improved model to address the mode-collapse problem, which involves machine learning techniques such as optimization and regularization. Therefore, it is also likely to belong to categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
